cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the performance analysis of a relay-based system, which involves the transmission of information. The use of channel side information (CSI) and shadowing side information (SSI) also relates to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the use of relay technology to improve the quality of service and extend the coverage area, which are important aspects of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper discusses the performance analysis of a communication system that uses relay technology. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a partial relay selection protocol for a dual-hop amplify-and-forward relaying system, which involves control of the relay selection process. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the use of relay technology in millimeter wave radio frequencies, which are commonly used for multimedia applications.
